Some gunmen suspected to be armed robbers have attacked a bullion van in Delta State.The bullion van belonging to a commercial bank was attacked at Otor-Owhe on the Ughelli-Asaba dual carriageway in Isoko North Local Government Area of the state. File photo used to illustrate story.



The details of the attack are still sketchy.The robbers were however said to have shot sporadically at the bullion van as the bullets bore holes on the windscreen of the vehicle conveying cash.More details later